             Axis (Apache eXtensible Interaction System)
             ------------------------------------------- 

Welcome to Axis!  You'll find documentation in the docs/ directory.

Please read the release notes (release-notes.html) in this directory for
details on the current release.

Thanks from all of us on the Axis team for downloading the package; help
us make it better by sending comments to axis-user@ws.apache.org.


Internally patched Axis 1.4 build
---------------------------------

This repository contains an internally patched Axis 1.4 build. The
patched delivery artifact is:

    axis/target/axis-1.4-statum-p1.jar

OWASP Dependency-Check identifies dependencies using artifact names,
coordinates and CPE metadata. Because this patched artifact remains
compatible with Axis 1.4, Dependency-Check may still report CVEs that
apply to the original Axis 1.4 distribution.

When delivering the patched JAR to a client, include these files:

    axis-1.4-statum-p1.jar
    dependency-check-suppressions.xml
    docs/security/axis-1.4-patched.md

The suppression file does not disable analysis for Axis in general. It
only suppresses the CVEs explicitly evaluated for this patched build.
The technical evidence and rationale are documented in:

    docs/security/axis-1.4-patched.md

To run OWASP Dependency-Check with the supplied suppressions, place
dependency-check-suppressions.xml next to the POM or verification script
used by the client and execute:

    mvn org.owasp:dependency-check-maven:12.1.9:check "-DsuppressionFiles=dependency-check-suppressions.xml"

If the client uses a dedicated verification POM, for example
pom-check.xml, run:

    mvn -f pom-check.xml org.owasp:dependency-check-maven:12.1.9:check "-DsuppressionFiles=dependency-check-suppressions.xml"

Alternatively, create a .mvn/maven.config file in the verification
directory with this content:

    -DsuppressionFiles=dependency-check-suppressions.xml

Then the regular Dependency-Check command will automatically use the
suppression file without hard-coded local paths.

